	<div id="instructions" class="center">
		<p>
			How to play: get as many anagrams as possible, using the letters on the board, within the time limit.<br>
	
			Start by choosing the board letters, by pressing 'c' for a consonant, or 'v' for a vowel.<br>
	
			Once you have chosen all 10 board letters, the 30 second timer will start.<br>
	
			When you think of a word, type it into the textbox, and press enter or tab.<br>
	
			The word will be saved below to be checked later.<br>
	
			You can't use a letter from the board more than once in a word.<br>
	
			A word is valid if it only uses letters on the board and is in later found in the dictionary.<br>	
	
			You can continue to enter words until the time runs out.
		</p>
		<p>
			Points: You get 1 point for each letter in a valid word.<br>
			If a word is not valid you lose 11 points minus the length of the word
			(short incorrect words are penalized more than long incorrect words).<br>
			Any valid word that is as long as the best possible anagram gets double points. 
		</p>
	</div>

